TITLE: Configuring and Rendering the Puck Editor Component
DESCRIPTION: React component implementation for the Puck editor. It includes component configuration with a HeadingBlock component that has a text field, defines initial data, and implements a save handler for persisting content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/measuredco/puck/blob/main/apps/docs/pages/docs/getting-started.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { Puck } from "@measured/puck";
import "@measured/puck/puck.css";

// Create Puck component config
const config = {
  components: {
    HeadingBlock: {
      fields: {
        children: {
          type: "text",
        },
      },
      render: ({ children }) => {
        return <h1>{children}</h1>;
      },
    },
  },
};

// Describe the initial data
const initialData = {};

// Save the data to your database
const save = (data) => {};

// Render Puck editor
export function Editor() {
  return <Puck config={config} data={initialData} onPublish={save} />;
}
```

