TITLE: Composing Custom Puck Editor Interface with TSX
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a custom editor interface by providing children to the Puck component. This example shows a grid layout with a preview and component list.
SOURCE: https://github.com/measuredco/puck/blob/main/apps/docs/pages/docs/extending-puck/custom-interfaces.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { Puck } from "@measured/puck";

export function Editor() {
  return (
    <Puck>
      <div
        style={{ display: "grid", gridTemplateColumns: "1fr 2fr", gridGap: 16 }}
      >
        <div>
          {/* Render the drag-and-drop preview */}
          <Puck.Preview />
        </div>
        <div>
          {/* Render the component list */}
          <Puck.Components />
        </div>
      </div>
    </Puck>
  );
}
```

