TITLE: Selector Pattern Examples with usePuck
DESCRIPTION: Shows good and bad practices for using selectors with usePuck to optimize performance and avoid re-renders.
SOURCE: https://github.com/measuredco/puck/blob/main/apps/docs/pages/docs/api-reference/functions/use-puck.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
// Good: only re-render when the `selectedItem` changes
const selectedItem = usePuck((s) => s.selectedItem);

// Bad: re-render when anything changes
const { selectedItem } = usePuck();
const { selectedItem } = usePuck((s) => s);

// Bad: selector creates a new object reference, causing an infinite comparison loop
const { selectedItem } = usePuck((s) => ({ ...s.selectedItem }));
```

